  Verified that the splicable flag is read correctly.

  Moved "END OF TRACE BUFFER" in dumpTraceBuf().

  Should not called dbgPrintf() before SetDemuxPar message from PPC is received.
  Instead, use tgtPrintf().  Then when SetDemuxPar is received, do a sendDebug()
  from beginning of buffer to current print pointer.

  Make TRAP a configuation, instead of compilation flag.

  Found a very weird bug, maybe in the compiler that in config.c, if I use
  more than 3 strcmp() in the routine, then the code doesn't work.


