6/14/00
  JC reports that the MUX responding problem only happens when DPI mode is
  set to 2!

  Plan for new time stamp mapping:
    There are four time bases:
      - local time
      - input time
      - output time
      - NTP time
    DVS 253 uses the input time.  Splicer needs to convert it to NTP time
    for the API message.

    The DSP has info for input to local time offset (tbOffset)
    The PPC should have the local time to NTP offset.
    We need to add PPC-DSP message for PPC to request tbOffset from DSP.

    To allow output time base mapping (i.e., each channel will be output
    at its own timebase, not according to local timebase), a new field,
    outTbOffset should be added in the ChanInfo structure.  This is the
    offset between the local time and the output time.

    So, we have:
        for each PCR channel, tbOffset = local time - input time
        for each channel, outTbOffset = local time - output time

    At channel setup,
        outTbOffset is initialized according to the first channel

    At splice point, 
        outTbOffset(new) = outTbOffset(old)

    Notice: DVS 353 splice_info_section() has a field pts_adjustment, which
    can be used for this purpose!!!


