6/22/00
  Jinbo has a log file which shows very long timeout problem: Timeout after
  2 min!?
  Problem seems to be due to the timeout check in splice control task applies
  only on channel with FG_SPLICE mode.  When the channel became FG_FINISHING
  mode, splice control will not timeout!  As a result, if the video is done,
  but audio or data never done, then we still cannot timeout!

  Modify the timeoutFlag to include checking in FINISHING mode.  However,
  I am not sure whether this will cause any other problem!!  Need to do
  extensive test here!

  After careful studying of the log, the above is NOT the reason.

  Added a set of counters in SwitchReq structure to count problems encounter
  during the switch.

  Also noticed in the log file that there is no field parity conflict
  or big tsDelay issues.  The only remaining issue I can think of is
  queue overflow!  But still, why didn't it timeout?

  Seems like TR adjustment does not work for closed GOP in frame based switch.
  Problem fixed.

  Stop responding to PPC polling when input or RC halted more than 500 ms.


